column13: First ρ in Barrabas is doubtful. For more discussion on the end of the line see preliminary report: "Chipping of the block cuts off the end of the word μνησθείης. Unfortunately the same cut descends to make doubtful the end of the reading. The letters given are clear but it is possible that other letters followed to make the second line into one name. As it stands, however, it is complete in itself, the individual expressing his wish in the temple of the god and subscribing himself as "in the presence of Zeus" or "near Zeus.""
